Camarillo.Conejo Grade:
The Conejo Grade is a 7% grade incline of the Ventura Freeway linking Thousand Oaks and cities of the Conejo Valley, with Camarillo and the cities on the Oxnard Plain. A Caltrans inspection station for trucks is stationed at the upper terminus of the grade.


== History ==
Land for the highway was originally part of the Rancho El Conejo, with contributions from Adolfo Camarillo.
